1
00:00:21,755 --> 00:00:28,461
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:02:15,535 --> 00:02:16,903
[BABY COOING]

3
00:02:18,271 --> 00:02:20,840
Oh. Oh, honey, you gotta
look at this one.

4
00:02:23,843 --> 00:02:26,513
This is great.

5
00:02:26,513 --> 00:02:29,916
Oh, this is great!
We should get Christmas cards
made up of these, right?

6
00:02:29,916 --> 00:02:32,585
Oh, this is great. Aw.
[PHONE RINGS]

7
00:02:32,785 --> 00:02:33,853
Hello.

8
00:02:34,921 --> 00:02:36,189
Hey, Bill. What's up?

9
00:02:36,856 --> 00:02:41,161
Oh, God. Why do these things
always come up on the weekends?

10
00:02:42,362 --> 00:02:44,264
Look, I'll run it through
on my computer here,

11
00:02:44,264 --> 00:02:46,199
and I'll call you
back tomorrow, all right?

12
00:02:46,199 --> 00:02:47,934
Oh, where do you think
you're going, Justin?

13
00:02:47,934 --> 00:02:50,203
All right. Bye-bye
[BABY COOING]

14
00:02:50,203 --> 00:02:51,771
Trying to make an escape,
huh, big guy?

15
00:02:51,771 --> 00:02:53,506
Ooh, watch it.

16
00:02:53,506 --> 00:02:58,511
Come on. Oh.
Come on. Come back. Whoo!

17
00:02:58,511 --> 00:03:00,413
Ooh, look, your favorite toys.
Come on, sit down.

18
00:03:00,413 --> 00:03:02,448
Ah, Mommy's gotta work.

19
00:03:02,448 --> 00:03:03,550
There you go.
Okay.

20
00:03:09,556 --> 00:03:10,523
I'll get this.

21
00:03:13,293 --> 00:03:15,528
Come on, sit down here.
Oh!

22
00:03:15,528 --> 00:03:17,197
Ah. Oh!
Ooh.

23
00:03:17,197 --> 00:03:19,432
[LAUGHS]
Don't ever stop that. Ever.

24
00:03:19,432 --> 00:03:21,367
You're so tensed,
you need a break.

25
00:03:21,367 --> 00:03:24,237
Oh, soon, soon.
[KISSES] How you doing?

26
00:03:24,237 --> 00:03:28,208
Well, Felder vs. United States
is getting all mixed up with
Arizona vs. Kincaid.

27
00:03:28,208 --> 00:03:30,977
Ooh. Hmm.
I thought freelancing was
gonna be a cinch, huh?

28
00:03:30,977 --> 00:03:32,245
Yeah, right.

29
00:03:32,245 --> 00:03:33,580
[PHONE RINGS]

30
00:03:35,415 --> 00:03:36,816
Hello!

31
00:03:36,816 --> 00:03:41,621
No, I'm sorry, she can't
come to the phone right now,
can I take a message?

32
00:03:41,621 --> 00:03:44,490
[BABY CRIES]
Justin!

33
00:03:54,634 --> 00:03:56,736
DR. SIRA:
I don't see any problem here.
The x-rays are fine,

34
00:03:56,736 --> 00:03:58,605
I'm certain
there's no concussion.

35
00:03:58,605 --> 00:04:01,007
Just a nasty bruise.
Oh, thank God.

36
00:04:01,007 --> 00:04:03,476
I feel so guilty.
No, no, it was my fault.

37
00:04:03,476 --> 00:04:05,345
Well, no harm done.

38
00:04:05,345 --> 00:04:07,480
A little liquid aspirin
will get him through the night.

39
00:04:07,480 --> 00:04:10,250
Be sure and have
your pediatrician take
a look at him in a day or two.

40
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:13,253
Thanks, Doc.
Thank you.
Come here, sweetie. Thank you.

41
00:04:13,253 --> 00:04:14,454
[ANNOUNCEMENT]
Dr. Robert Gray...

42
00:04:14,454 --> 00:04:16,322
Come on, let's go.
You okay, big guy?

43
00:04:16,322 --> 00:04:18,691
...Dr. Robert Gray, line 2.

44
00:04:33,673 --> 00:04:35,708
[BABY COOS]

45
00:04:35,708 --> 00:04:39,345
Shh, shh, shh, shh.
It's time
to go to sleep, big guy.

46
00:04:48,888 --> 00:04:49,756
[FLOORBOARD CREAKS]

47
00:04:59,299 --> 00:05:01,567
Are you not
coming to bed, honey?
It's about ten o'clock.

48
00:05:01,567 --> 00:05:03,636
Oh, I know. I still have ways
to go on this brief.

49
00:05:03,636 --> 00:05:05,872
I promised them
I'll have it done by Friday.

50
00:05:05,872 --> 00:05:09,008
Hey, no one wants
to watch you burn out.

51
00:05:09,008 --> 00:05:10,877
Hey, you know what,
I'm gonna go get
you a cappuccino.

52
00:05:10,877 --> 00:05:12,645
You're gonna
need the caffeine.
Ooh, thank you.

53
00:05:12,645 --> 00:05:14,781
Oh, do me a favor.
Would you turn on
Justin's monitor

54
00:05:14,781 --> 00:05:16,616
before you go?
I forgot to do it.
Sure.

55
00:05:16,616 --> 00:05:19,852
Thank you. I love you.
[CHUCKLES]

56
00:05:23,990 --> 00:05:25,692
Okay.

57
00:05:36,035 --> 00:05:40,039
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYS]

58
00:07:01,654 --> 00:07:06,058
[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

59
00:07:15,735 --> 00:07:19,505
[BABY CRYING]

60
00:07:20,740 --> 00:07:23,443
♪ Rock-a-by baby

61
00:07:24,043 --> 00:07:27,046
♪ On the tree top

62
00:07:27,046 --> 00:07:32,485
♪ When the wind blows
The cradle will rock

63
00:07:32,485 --> 00:07:37,190
♪ When the bough breaks
The cradle will fall...

64
00:07:37,190 --> 00:07:39,759
Coffee and a lullaby?
What a guy.
♪ And down will fall baby

65
00:07:40,693 --> 00:07:42,462
♪ Cradle and all ♪

66
00:07:43,529 --> 00:07:45,665
[BABY CRIES]
Shh. It's okay.

67
00:07:45,932 --> 00:07:47,733
No, no.

68
00:07:50,970 --> 00:07:52,839
Hmm. Ugh.

69
00:07:57,543 --> 00:08:00,213
I love your singing voice,
honey, but when're you
gonna go on that coffee run?

70
00:08:02,215 --> 00:08:04,951
One cappuccino, madam,
with a dash of cinnamon.

71
00:08:04,951 --> 00:08:07,753
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYS]

72
00:08:14,026 --> 00:08:17,163
[BABY CRYING]
Shh. Don't cry, now.
Shh. Come on.

73
00:08:17,163 --> 00:08:20,166
Come on, shh, shh, shh.

74
00:08:20,166 --> 00:08:21,601
It's okay.

75
00:08:30,710 --> 00:08:32,979
Honey, all the doors
and windows are locked.
Nobody's been in here.

76
00:08:32,979 --> 00:08:34,881
It's just really strange,
you know?

77
00:08:36,649 --> 00:08:39,752
Uh, maybe,
maybe you were listening
in on someone else's monitor.

78
00:08:40,786 --> 00:08:42,822
Is that possible?

79
00:08:42,822 --> 00:08:44,824
Well, yeah, I think so.
I mean, these things
only operate

80
00:08:44,824 --> 00:08:48,861
You know how many parents
out there have
this kind of monitor?

81
00:08:50,296 --> 00:08:51,163
Yeah, I guess so.

82
00:08:52,865 --> 00:08:55,201
It just really spooked me.
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

83
00:09:02,808 --> 00:09:06,145
[BABY CRIES]

84
00:09:06,145 --> 00:09:08,314
[ENGINE REVS]

85
00:09:19,292 --> 00:09:22,662
[INDISTINCT YELLING]

86
00:09:22,662 --> 00:09:24,630
MAN:
Gotta do the air runs first.

87
00:09:29,035 --> 00:09:31,237
Hey, Brian!
You got a minute?

88
00:09:31,237 --> 00:09:32,638
Sure, what's the problem?

89
00:09:32,638 --> 00:09:34,807
Last night, the pilot
reported a mod C failure

90
00:09:34,807 --> 00:09:36,075
at about 20,000 feet.

91
00:09:36,075 --> 00:09:40,846
Hey, what happened
to you last night
sounds kinda weird.

92
00:09:40,846 --> 00:09:43,316
Yeah, now, Donna
want a home security system.

93
00:09:43,316 --> 00:09:47,219
Yeah? We have one of those.
Keep it stashed
under the mattress.

94
00:09:47,219 --> 00:09:49,855
Hey, listen, I think
we better do
a static system test.

95
00:09:49,855 --> 00:09:51,757
We may have
a little moisture in here.

96
00:09:51,757 --> 00:09:54,994
Could be. I've checked
all the lines,
and nothings crossed.

97
00:09:54,994 --> 00:09:56,896
What's that you said
about your security system?

98
00:09:56,896 --> 00:09:58,898
Oh, I have a .357 magnum.

99
00:10:01,133 --> 00:10:04,136
Donna wouldn't want
a gun in the house
with Justin crawling around.

100
00:10:04,136 --> 00:10:06,706
Well, an alarm will take care
of most burglars,

101
00:10:06,706 --> 00:10:09,675
but it's the crazies
I'm worried about.
Only one thing will stop them.

102
00:10:13,813 --> 00:10:15,014
[BABY COOING]

103
00:10:17,383 --> 00:10:21,220
Well, aside from the bruise,
you have a perfectly healthy
1-year-old.

104
00:10:21,220 --> 00:10:24,390
23 pounds, 30 inches,
right in the normal range.

105
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:26,959
I think you have an athlete
on your hands there.

106
00:10:26,959 --> 00:10:28,961
He's terrific.
We're the ones
who need work.

107
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:33,399
Look, Donna,
let me tell you something.

108
00:10:33,399 --> 00:10:37,203
Many of the big changes
in your life will happen
over time, slowly,

109
00:10:37,203 --> 00:10:41,140
but when you have a baby,
ooh, it's like that.

110
00:10:41,140 --> 00:10:45,244
Overnight your life changes.
Forever. Takes a little time
to get used to it.

111
00:10:48,381 --> 00:10:52,151
SALESMAN: The Centaur 3000
monitors up to
12 different areas.

112
00:10:52,151 --> 00:10:55,021
It actually tells you
when any door or window is open,

113
00:10:55,021 --> 00:10:56,355
even when
the system isn't armed.

114
00:10:58,024 --> 00:11:01,327
Zone one. Security alert.
Door open.

115
00:11:03,095 --> 00:11:06,732
In the event of a break-in,
a distress signal
is instantly sent

116
00:11:06,732 --> 00:11:08,868
to hour 24-hour
monitoring station.

117
00:11:08,868 --> 00:11:13,005
If you press
the emergency button,
the police are summoned as well.

118
00:11:13,005 --> 00:11:14,840
I like it.
I think we should get it.

119
00:11:16,942 --> 00:11:19,412
How long does it take
for the police to get here
after the alarm's triggered.

120
00:11:19,412 --> 00:11:20,946
No more than ten minutes.

121
00:11:20,946 --> 00:11:23,115
What is some psycho breaks in?

122
00:11:23,115 --> 00:11:25,151
I mean, he could kill us all
and be gone in two.

123
00:11:25,151 --> 00:11:28,854
With all due respect, McDermott,
no alarm system
will stop a psycho.

124
00:11:28,854 --> 00:11:30,923
But ours will certainly
deter one.

125
00:11:37,396 --> 00:11:38,731
How soon can you install it?

126
00:11:40,700 --> 00:11:43,869
[CHATTERING]

127
00:11:54,013 --> 00:11:55,081
Hello, Joan.

128
00:11:56,215 --> 00:11:58,050
Looking tense.

129
00:11:58,050 --> 00:11:59,919
You said 7:30,
it's almost 8:00.

130
00:12:00,953 --> 00:12:02,955
I'm sorry,
I had an important client.

131
00:12:02,955 --> 00:12:05,758
You're sorry?
That's all you can say?
I said hot tea!

132
00:12:07,393 --> 00:12:10,930
Relax, you're doing great.

133
00:12:10,930 --> 00:12:13,766
There hasn't been a word
on the news
or in the papers.

134
00:12:15,301 --> 00:12:16,235
I'm fine.

135
00:12:22,007 --> 00:12:25,077
$5,000. 25% as agreed.

136
00:12:26,078 --> 00:12:27,813
Thank you.
You earned it.

137
00:12:33,152 --> 00:12:34,153
I found another one.

138
00:12:35,955 --> 00:12:37,022
In Northside.

139
00:12:45,030 --> 00:12:47,500
Yaay!

140
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:49,168
Oh, Mommy's gotta get dressed.

141
00:12:50,302 --> 00:12:51,904
Have you seen my black belt?

142
00:12:51,904 --> 00:12:53,038
Yeah, it's in the closet.

143
00:12:53,773 --> 00:12:55,975
I just looked.

144
00:12:55,975 --> 00:12:57,409
I'll just wear the brown one.
Hey, buddy.

145
00:12:59,044 --> 00:13:02,448
Hmm. Hmm. Hmm.

146
00:13:02,448 --> 00:13:04,116
Mm. We're really
running late, honey.

147
00:13:04,116 --> 00:13:07,086
No, we're not.
Besides, the Avila's
will understand.

148
00:13:10,189 --> 00:13:13,058
You okay, tiger?
Oh. Aw. You okay?

149
00:13:13,058 --> 00:13:15,795
It's time to play big, big guy.

150
00:13:15,795 --> 00:13:17,429
We need to baby-proof
this room a lot better.
Come here.

151
00:13:23,803 --> 00:13:25,237
Kitty, kitty, kitty, kitty.

152
00:13:26,572 --> 00:13:27,873
Ryan, your black belt is right--

153
00:13:33,546 --> 00:13:36,148
Now, where were we?

154
00:13:40,986 --> 00:13:42,855
I know.

155
00:13:42,855 --> 00:13:45,224
I know. I was gonna tell you
about it on the drive over.

156
00:13:45,224 --> 00:13:48,060
How could you buy something
like this without discussing
it with me first?

157
00:13:48,060 --> 00:13:50,462
I know, you're right.
But I-I didn't buy it,

158
00:13:50,462 --> 00:13:51,530
Bill lent it to me.

159
00:13:51,530 --> 00:13:53,899
We've got a baby in the house.

160
00:13:53,899 --> 00:13:56,836
Even the security guy said
no system will stop a psycho.

161
00:13:56,836 --> 00:14:00,406
I-I've even
hidden the bullets in
a completely different drawer.

162
00:14:00,406 --> 00:14:02,274
I still want it
out of here, okay?

163
00:14:02,274 --> 00:14:04,310
[DOORBELL RINGS]

164
00:14:06,245 --> 00:14:07,313
It'll be gone tomorrow.

165
00:14:08,147 --> 00:14:09,181
Thanks, honey.

166
00:14:17,356 --> 00:14:19,491
Zone one. Door open.

167
00:14:19,491 --> 00:14:21,193
Hi, I'm Rachel.

168
00:14:23,395 --> 00:14:26,332
The babysitter.
Oh. Oh, I'm sorry.
Come on in.

169
00:14:32,171 --> 00:14:34,273
Honey, the babysitters here.
[BABY YELLING]

170
00:14:34,273 --> 00:14:36,508
Oh. Hi.

171
00:14:36,508 --> 00:14:38,344
Hi.
Oh, hi, Rachel.

172
00:14:38,344 --> 00:14:40,212
Susan couldn't
make it tonight.

173
00:14:40,212 --> 00:14:42,114
But she gave Rachel
very high marks.

174
00:14:42,114 --> 00:14:44,083
Listen, Justin's
already been fed.

175
00:14:44,083 --> 00:14:46,986
The phone number we're
going to be at is by the phone
on a Post-It.

176
00:14:46,986 --> 00:14:50,322
just in case
it accidentally goes off.
[BABY YELLING]

177
00:14:50,322 --> 00:14:52,124
Okay, great.

178
00:14:52,124 --> 00:14:53,525
Well, come meet Justin.
He looks like
he wants to meet you.

179
00:14:53,525 --> 00:14:55,895
Yeah. Hi, sweetheart.
[BABY YELLING]

180
00:14:55,895 --> 00:15:00,199
Baby. [LAUGHS] You are
just about the cutest

181
00:15:00,199 --> 00:15:02,001
little boy I've seen
in my whole life.

182
00:15:02,001 --> 00:15:03,068
Yes.
Excuse me.

183
00:15:03,068 --> 00:15:05,070
He looks just like his dad.

184
00:15:05,070 --> 00:15:07,339
Hey, thanks for letting
Mom and Dad have
the night off, tiger.

185
00:15:07,339 --> 00:15:08,941
Go easy on Rachel,
we don't wanna scare her off.

186
00:15:08,941 --> 00:15:10,409
Oh, no chance of that.

187
00:15:10,409 --> 00:15:12,011
We shouldn't be too late.

188
00:15:12,011 --> 00:15:13,312
Okay.

189
00:15:16,582 --> 00:15:18,584
BRIAN: This dinner
looks incredible, Kay.
KAY: Thank you.

190
00:15:18,584 --> 00:15:20,619
[CHUCKLES]
I'd like to when you had time
to cook all this

191
00:15:20,619 --> 00:15:23,923
I gotta tell you,
I don't know
how she does it.

192
00:15:23,923 --> 00:15:25,224
Hey, I've been
saying the same thing.

193
00:15:25,224 --> 00:15:29,628
On top of that,
Donna has been on the computer
every single night

194
00:15:29,628 --> 00:15:32,464
working on
a freelance assignment
until midnight.

195
00:15:32,464 --> 00:15:34,500
Actually, the firm
has offered me
a permanent position.

196
00:15:36,468 --> 00:15:38,671
Hey.

197
00:15:38,671 --> 00:15:41,607
It's only three clients,
it's no big deal, but they'll
let me work out of the house.

198
00:15:41,607 --> 00:15:43,375
That's wonderful.

199
00:15:43,375 --> 00:15:45,010
That's fantastic, honey.

200
00:15:45,311 --> 00:15:47,012
Thanks.

201
00:15:47,012 --> 00:15:49,448
Well, I guess you're gonna be
hiring a nanny now, huh?

202
00:15:49,448 --> 00:15:51,684
Well, we already have someone
who comes into help
with the housework,

203
00:15:51,684 --> 00:15:53,385
I'll ask her her to
give us some more time,

204
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:56,689
but, uh, we wanna be the ones
to raise Justin.

205
00:15:56,689 --> 00:15:58,991
Yes, but there are only
so many hours in the day.

206
00:15:59,591 --> 00:16:01,060
Brian and I can handle it.

207
00:16:01,727 --> 00:16:03,529
Yeah. Sure.

208
00:16:03,529 --> 00:16:07,232
[ROCK MUSIC PLAYING]

209
00:16:22,181 --> 00:16:24,616
Zone one. Security alert.

210
00:16:32,491 --> 00:16:34,360
Oh, God, you scared me.

211
00:16:38,564 --> 00:16:40,366
Guess I should have shouted out
that we were home.

212
00:16:41,333 --> 00:16:42,668
Yeah, you're right.
I'm sorry.

213
00:16:42,668 --> 00:16:46,038
I, uh, I shouldn't have
had it up so loud.

214
00:16:46,038 --> 00:16:49,708
Oh, yeah, right after you left.
He's an angel.

215
00:16:49,708 --> 00:16:51,343
Okay, here you go.

216
00:16:51,343 --> 00:16:53,245
Ah, thank you.
Let me give you a ride home.

217
00:16:53,245 --> 00:16:54,513
Okay, great.

218
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:56,281
Be a few minutes.

219
00:16:57,182 --> 00:16:58,550
Good night.
Bye bye.

220
00:17:18,771 --> 00:17:20,806
Psych major, huh?

221
00:17:20,806 --> 00:17:23,642
Oh, no, I,
I just like psychology.

222
00:17:23,642 --> 00:17:25,344
Yeah?

223
00:17:25,344 --> 00:17:30,349
It's fascinating. People
don't always do
things that make sense.

224
00:17:31,150 --> 00:17:32,351
What do you mean?

225
00:17:32,351 --> 00:17:34,053
Well, we all have impulses.

226
00:17:34,053 --> 00:17:37,823
Greed, power, love, sex.

227
00:17:39,792 --> 00:17:42,094
It's just a question
of whether or not
you act on them.

228
00:17:44,830 --> 00:17:47,366
So, did Justin
give you any problems?

229
00:17:48,834 --> 00:17:51,370
No, Mr. McDermott.
Justin was
no problem at all.

230
00:17:53,572 --> 00:17:54,440
Good.

231
00:18:07,286 --> 00:18:09,588
[ON TV]
Kate, I had to do something...

232
00:18:09,588 --> 00:18:11,323
Finally got him
to go back to sleep.

233
00:18:11,623 --> 00:18:13,525
Come here.

234
00:18:13,525 --> 00:18:15,360
Mm. Mm.

235
00:18:20,499 --> 00:18:23,535
I don't know
if it's the wine or what,
but I'm dead tired.

236
00:18:30,809 --> 00:18:32,377
What?
Nothing.

237
00:18:34,613 --> 00:18:36,715
