476
00:33:34,512 --> 00:33:36,347
Yeah, I know, I know
it was fine in the morning.

477
00:33:37,682 --> 00:33:38,549
Oh, damn it!

478
00:33:41,386 --> 00:33:44,389
All right, listen,
I'll see if I can get a sitter
and I'll call you back.

479
00:33:45,723 --> 00:33:47,158
Okay, all right.

480
00:33:53,464 --> 00:33:54,632
[DOORBELL RINGS]

481
00:33:57,268 --> 00:33:59,137
Hi. All right.
Hey, come on in.

482
00:34:02,774 --> 00:34:05,643
Listen thanks for coming
on such short notice.
Oh, no problem.

483
00:34:05,643 --> 00:34:07,678
Justin's asleep in his room.
I have the monitor
out in the den.

484
00:34:07,678 --> 00:34:09,147
I really shouldn't be that long.

485
00:34:10,081 --> 00:34:12,250
Bad timing, huh?

486
00:34:12,250 --> 00:34:14,485
Your wife has to
go out of town,
you have to go into work.

487
00:34:14,485 --> 00:34:18,523
My number at work
is by the phone, just in case
you need to reach me.

488
00:34:18,523 --> 00:34:21,092
Don't worry about Justin.
He's in very good hands.

489
00:34:21,626 --> 00:34:22,693
Thanks again.

490
00:34:27,832 --> 00:34:30,134
Zone one. Door open.

491
00:34:30,501 --> 00:34:33,137
[KEYPAD BEEPS]

492
00:35:04,202 --> 00:35:06,637
So, tell me about
this babysitter.

493
00:35:09,173 --> 00:35:10,775
Your fantasy life
a little slow?

494
00:35:10,775 --> 00:35:14,445
No, just my real life.
The in-laws are in this weekend.

495
00:35:14,445 --> 00:35:16,214
I'm sorry to hear that.

496
00:35:16,214 --> 00:35:18,282
So, back to the babysitter.

497
00:35:18,282 --> 00:35:22,153
I can see it now. You come in,
she's got a nice fire burning

498
00:35:22,153 --> 00:35:24,455
couple of glasses
of Cabernet poured.

499
00:35:24,455 --> 00:35:27,525
She's wearing one of those
numbers from Victoria's Secret.

500
00:35:30,428 --> 00:35:33,764
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

501
00:35:38,402 --> 00:35:40,438
[THUNDERCLAPS]

502
00:35:54,719 --> 00:35:57,155
[RAIN PATTERING]

503
00:35:57,622 --> 00:35:59,724
[THUNDERCLAP]

504
00:36:07,765 --> 00:36:08,866
That should take care of it.

505
00:36:08,866 --> 00:36:11,369
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

506
00:36:11,369 --> 00:36:12,770
I can't wait to
drive home in that.

507
00:36:13,504 --> 00:36:14,872
Yeah, you and me both.

508
00:36:28,886 --> 00:36:30,855
[THUNDERCLAPS]

509
00:36:30,855 --> 00:36:33,958
[KEYPAD BEEPS]
[DOOR OPENS]

510
00:36:33,958 --> 00:36:35,493
Hey, you're home early.

511
00:36:37,495 --> 00:36:38,763
So how did it go?

512
00:36:40,565 --> 00:36:41,632
Brian?

513
00:36:43,234 --> 00:36:43,901
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

514
00:36:48,306 --> 00:36:50,641
Oh, my God.
You're soaked!

515
00:36:51,809 --> 00:36:53,778
I forgot my umbrella.

516
00:36:53,778 --> 00:36:55,580
Listen, I gotta change clothes,
how's Justin?

517
00:36:56,347 --> 00:36:57,582
Not a peep.

518
00:36:58,583 --> 00:36:59,650
Good.

519
00:37:04,922 --> 00:37:08,926
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

520
00:37:08,926 --> 00:37:10,928
[THUNDERCLAP]

521
00:37:46,931 --> 00:37:51,836
[EERIE MUSIC PLAYING]

522
00:38:10,888 --> 00:38:12,556
I'll have to write you a check.

523
00:38:12,556 --> 00:38:13,691
Oh, it's no problem.

524
00:38:16,460 --> 00:38:19,964
You know, I was thinking
it's, it's gonna take forever
to get a cab in this weather.

525
00:38:19,964 --> 00:38:22,600
Maybe we just wait
for the rain to let up.

526
00:38:24,468 --> 00:38:25,770
You think that's a good idea?

527
00:38:35,379 --> 00:38:36,647
Rachel...

528
00:38:38,783 --> 00:38:42,853
[MUSIC SLOWLY INTENSIFIES]

529
00:38:56,500 --> 00:38:58,803
Zone three. Security alert.

530
00:39:05,776 --> 00:39:08,512
[BABY CRIES]
Shh. Shh.

531
00:39:10,014 --> 00:39:12,650
It's okay. It's okay.

532
00:39:15,820 --> 00:39:16,787
That's it.

533
00:39:20,991 --> 00:39:23,794
Rachel, this is a mistake.
I can't do this.

534
00:39:25,863 --> 00:39:27,631
I'll call you a cab.

535
00:39:27,631 --> 00:39:28,733
[BABY CRIES]

536
00:39:29,900 --> 00:39:32,136
[BABY CRIES]

537
00:39:35,806 --> 00:39:37,141
[BABY CRIES]

538
00:39:37,141 --> 00:39:40,611
I'll be right back.
We have to talk about this.

539
00:39:43,714 --> 00:39:49,820
♪ Rock-a-by baby
On the tree top

540
00:39:49,820 --> 00:39:52,890
♪ When the wind blows
The cradle-- ♪

541
00:39:53,591 --> 00:39:55,393
[GUNSHOTS]

542
00:39:55,393 --> 00:39:56,827
Brian!

543
00:40:01,132 --> 00:40:03,167
[ALARM BLARING]

544
00:40:16,747 --> 00:40:21,452
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

545
00:40:33,030 --> 00:40:34,198
Mrs. McDermott?

546
00:40:34,799 --> 00:40:36,600
Yes?

547
00:40:36,600 --> 00:40:38,569
Portland police.
Can we talk to you
for a minute?

548
00:40:38,969 --> 00:40:39,837
Police?

549
00:40:39,837 --> 00:40:42,440
Can I see
some identification, please?

550
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:44,542
Certainly.
I'm Detective Tauber,

551
00:40:44,542 --> 00:40:45,743
this is my partner,
Detective Pruso.

552
00:40:47,445 --> 00:40:49,180
What is it? Is it my husband?

553
00:40:49,180 --> 00:40:51,015
I'm afraid we don't have
the whole picture yet, ma'am.

554
00:40:51,015 --> 00:40:53,083
But apparently there's been
an incident at your house.

555
00:40:53,083 --> 00:40:56,120
It seems an intruder
broke in through
the nursery window.

556
00:40:56,120 --> 00:40:59,757
Now, the intruder got away,
but I'm sorry to have
to tell you

557
00:40:59,757 --> 00:41:00,858
he took your son with him.

558
00:41:02,493 --> 00:41:04,662
Justin was kidnapped?

559
00:41:04,662 --> 00:41:06,797
That's the assumption
everyone is working on
at the moment, ma'am.

560
00:41:06,797 --> 00:41:09,467
Now, we're going to
take you to the airport as soon
as you're ready to travel.

561
00:41:09,467 --> 00:41:11,135
Are you all right?
I gotta call Brian.

562
00:41:11,135 --> 00:41:13,804
Oh, my baby!
Make it a quick call, ma'am!

563
00:41:13,804 --> 00:41:15,105
They wanna keep
the phone lines clear.

564
00:41:21,946 --> 00:41:27,485
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

565
00:41:36,727 --> 00:41:38,829
First thing
in the morning, all right?
You have my card.

566
00:41:38,829 --> 00:41:40,030
Okay, thanks.

567
00:41:43,968 --> 00:41:46,871
Lieutenant?
There are no prints,
some smudges.

568
00:41:46,871 --> 00:41:48,772
10:1 he was wearing gloves.

569
00:41:51,909 --> 00:41:53,911
How about that, Mr. McDermott,
was he wearing gloves?

570
00:41:56,714 --> 00:42:00,651
Maybe. I, I really
can't remember.

571
00:42:00,651 --> 00:42:02,052
Is there anything
else you can recall?

572
00:42:07,057 --> 00:42:09,727
Mr. McDermott.

573
00:42:09,727 --> 00:42:15,099
If we don't find the victim
within the first eight hours,
our odds go way down.

574
00:42:15,099 --> 00:42:18,736
Now, I know this is tough,
but you gotta set aside your
feelings for a little while,

575
00:42:18,736 --> 00:42:20,271
and think hard,
for your son's sake.

576
00:42:26,710 --> 00:42:28,546
All I know was what I told you.

577
00:42:31,015 --> 00:42:32,316
He was a tall guy.

578
00:42:47,998 --> 00:42:49,667
OFFICER:
Mrs. McDermott?

579
00:42:59,610 --> 00:43:00,778
Brian...

580
00:43:17,861 --> 00:43:19,330
That's where he came in.

581
00:43:25,169 --> 00:43:26,170
Mrs. McDermott

582
00:43:27,838 --> 00:43:30,341
I'm Lt. Dugger,
I'm heading up
the investigation.

583
00:43:30,341 --> 00:43:32,910
I know how upsetting
this must be to you,

584
00:43:32,910 --> 00:43:34,845
but I have a few questions
I need to ask.

585
00:43:36,714 --> 00:43:39,617
Does Justin
have any distinguishing
marks or scars?

586
00:43:39,617 --> 00:43:40,784
A birthmark maybe?

587
00:43:41,118 --> 00:43:42,186
No.

588
00:43:42,186 --> 00:43:43,721
Yes.

589
00:43:43,721 --> 00:43:45,689
He has a burn on his right arm.

590
00:43:45,689 --> 00:43:48,759
Oh, that's right.
I was thinking about birthmarks.

591
00:43:48,759 --> 00:43:50,928
Right arm?
Above or below the elbow?

592
00:43:52,029 --> 00:43:53,831
Right here.

593
00:43:53,831 --> 00:43:55,699
I've already asked
your husband this, but,

594
00:43:55,699 --> 00:43:58,235
is there anyone you can think of
who might wanna harm you?

595
00:43:58,235 --> 00:44:00,004
Someone holding
a grudge of any kind?

596
00:44:00,270 --> 00:44:02,239
No. No one.

597
00:44:02,239 --> 00:44:05,009
I mean, come on we're not rich.
Why would someone
wanna take our baby?

598
00:44:05,743 --> 00:44:07,945
I'm not sure, ma'am.

599
00:44:07,945 --> 00:44:11,815
We put a tap on your phone.
And I'm leaving officers here
to monitor your calls.

600
00:44:11,815 --> 00:44:14,785
If you have to go out,
we'll forward any calls to you
on your cell phone.

601
00:44:14,785 --> 00:44:15,719
We've got it all worked out.

602
00:44:15,719 --> 00:44:17,688
What about the FBI?

603
00:44:17,688 --> 00:44:20,758
Um, they've been contacted.
They're working on it
from their end.

604
00:44:22,760 --> 00:44:26,930
Try not to worry,
Mrs. McDermott, we're working
hard to get your son back.

605
00:44:26,930 --> 00:44:28,666
I'll call you as soon as
I have something.

606
00:44:29,133 --> 00:44:30,067
Thank you.

607
00:44:36,440 --> 00:44:37,941
[SIGHS]

608
00:44:37,941 --> 00:44:40,077
OFFICER ON RADIO:
At code 30...

609
00:44:41,412 --> 00:44:43,347
Lieutenant.

610
00:44:43,347 --> 00:44:45,683
It's a dead ringer
for the Northside
abduction, isn't it?

611
00:44:45,683 --> 00:44:47,951
Sure is.

612
00:44:47,951 --> 00:44:49,987
Or maybe that's
what somebody wants us to think.

613
00:44:52,389 --> 00:44:53,457
[CAR DOOR OPENS]

614
00:44:55,893 --> 00:44:58,929
How could you have done
something so stupid?

615
00:44:58,929 --> 00:45:01,465
You're not the one
on the firing line, okay?

616
00:45:01,465 --> 00:45:04,068
For all I know,
he could have had a gun, too.

617
00:45:04,068 --> 00:45:07,171
This isn't an armed robbery
at a mini mart, Robert.

618
00:45:07,171 --> 00:45:11,141
If you get caught,
no one is going to be able
to get you off. Not even me.

619
00:45:11,141 --> 00:45:12,109
I'm not gonna get caught.

620
00:45:15,079 --> 00:45:17,748
If you wanna work for me,
if you wanna live here,

621
00:45:19,717 --> 00:45:20,884
then you'll give me that gun.

622
00:45:23,387 --> 00:45:24,388
Right now.

623
00:45:43,941 --> 00:45:45,442
What's this?

624
00:45:45,442 --> 00:45:46,777
I think it's a burn.

625
00:45:48,278 --> 00:45:49,346
A burn?

626
00:45:50,414 --> 00:45:51,749
Yeah, is that a problem?

627
00:45:52,783 --> 00:45:56,386
A burn is identifiable, Robert.

628
00:45:56,386 --> 00:46:00,190
We're going to have to
keep him here until we can
get rid of this bandage.

629
00:46:10,400 --> 00:46:12,469
FEMALE OFFICER ON RADIO:
7A 43, state again.

630
00:46:12,469 --> 00:46:14,538
OFFICER 1: Ana Lauren?
OFFICER 2: Yeah, we
got here here.

631
00:46:15,506 --> 00:46:16,907
That should do it.

632
00:46:31,155 --> 00:46:34,858
I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.

633
00:46:36,326 --> 00:46:38,996
I'm so selfish,
I had to go for
that stupid seminar.

634
00:46:38,996 --> 00:46:41,064
I should have been home
taking care of my baby.

635
00:46:41,064 --> 00:46:43,233
It wasn't your fault.
It wasn't your fault.
He took my son.

636
00:46:45,402 --> 00:46:46,436
It's mine.

637
00:46:59,316 --> 00:47:01,151
There's something
I need to talk to you about.

638
00:47:03,320 --> 00:47:04,922
[DOORBELL RINGS]

639
00:47:19,369 --> 00:47:20,437
We just heard.

640
00:47:21,471 --> 00:47:22,973
Come on in.

641
00:47:28,545 --> 00:47:29,947
[DOOR SHUTS]

642
00:47:32,182 --> 00:47:34,384
We thought you probably
wouldn't feel
like cooking late.

643
00:47:34,384 --> 00:47:35,986
So, Kay made a casserole.

644
00:47:37,087 --> 00:47:39,223
God, Brian, we're so sorry.

645
00:47:39,223 --> 00:47:40,157
Thanks.

646
00:47:41,091 --> 00:47:42,192
Have you heard
anything yet?

647
00:47:42,960 --> 00:47:44,228
No.

648
00:47:44,228 --> 00:47:45,929
Well, if there's
anything we can do.

649
00:47:45,929 --> 00:47:48,031
[PHONE RINGS]

650
00:47:56,173 --> 00:47:57,174
Hello?

651
00:47:58,442 --> 00:47:59,576
Yes, Lieutenant?

652
00:48:02,613 --> 00:48:03,881
We'll be right down.

653
00:48:06,049 --> 00:48:07,885
I know you didn't see the man,

654
00:48:07,885 --> 00:48:11,121
but you may been watched
over a period of time
for the last few days.

655
00:48:11,121 --> 00:48:14,258
Um, do one of these faces
ring a bell?

656
00:48:14,258 --> 00:48:17,628
if you could help me
with a couple other things,
Mr. McDermott?

657
00:48:17,628 --> 00:48:19,496
In my office?
Yeah. Sure.

658
00:48:21,665 --> 00:48:24,034
You'll be okay. All right?

659
00:48:28,906 --> 00:48:30,240
What do you need?

660
00:48:30,240 --> 00:48:32,309
Just a little privacy.
Have a seat.

661
00:48:33,977 --> 00:48:35,279
Can I call you Brian?

662
00:48:36,513 --> 00:48:39,283
Sure.
So, Brian.

663
00:48:39,283 --> 00:48:41,184
Anything you've forgotten
to tell me about?

664
00:48:41,652 --> 00:48:43,353
Like what?

665
00:48:43,353 --> 00:48:48,125
Well, I, uh,
I talked to Rachel Edmond
this morning.

666
00:48:48,125 --> 00:48:51,161
You sorta forgot to mention
you two being in the bedroom
las night.

667
00:48:52,129 --> 00:48:56,166
No, no, I don't care
what you were doing
with the babysitter.

668
00:48:57,200 --> 00:48:58,669
What I'm interested in
is the baby.

669
00:48:58,669 --> 00:49:03,941
Well, I'm concerned about
what else you might have
neglected to mention.

670
00:49:03,941 --> 00:49:06,610
Like the fact that your son
had a bad burn on his arm.

671
00:49:06,610 --> 00:49:08,211
You asked about birthmarks.

672
00:49:08,211 --> 00:49:10,948
No, I asked about
identifying marks.

673
00:49:11,515 --> 00:49:12,950
How did he get burned anyway?

674
00:49:12,950 --> 00:49:14,318
It was an accident.

675
00:49:14,318 --> 00:49:16,286
He pulled on the cord,
and the iron fell.

676
00:49:16,286 --> 00:49:18,155
Does your son
have a lot of accidents?

677
00:49:18,722 --> 00:49:19,990
What're you getting at?

678
00:49:23,427 --> 00:49:25,295
I'm just trying to get
the whole picture here, Brian.

679
00:49:36,340 --> 00:49:38,408
[DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES]

680
00:49:42,045 --> 00:49:43,380
Have you heard anything?

681
00:49:43,380 --> 00:49:44,247
Mm-hmm.

682
00:49:50,153 --> 00:49:52,289
Could you give us
a couple of minutes
alone, please?

683
00:49:52,622 --> 00:49:53,690
Yeah.

684
00:50:04,468 --> 00:50:06,069
I can't stop thinking about him.

685
00:50:07,104 --> 00:50:10,340
You know?
I mean, is he cold?

686
00:50:10,741 --> 00:50:12,409
Is he hungry?

687
00:50:20,050 --> 00:50:23,020
Donna there's something I think
you should know about
what happened last night.

688
00:50:23,020 --> 00:50:24,654
What? What is it?

689
00:50:27,324 --> 00:50:29,626
The moment he broke in,
I was in the bedroom.

690
00:50:29,626 --> 00:50:33,130
I got caught in the rain,
and I had to change
my clothes.

691
00:50:33,130 --> 00:50:34,297
You already told me that.

692
00:50:40,604 --> 00:50:42,105
I wasn't alone.

693
00:50:43,106 --> 00:50:44,174
Rachel was with me.

694
00:50:46,243 --> 00:50:50,047
She came in to tell me
it might take a while
to get a cab. So--

695
00:50:50,047 --> 00:50:52,215
What do you mean with you?

696
00:50:54,251 --> 00:50:56,620
It was just a kiss.
Nothing happened, really.

697
00:50:58,822 --> 00:51:01,291
You mean to stand here

698
00:51:01,291 --> 00:51:03,260
and tell me that
while your son
was being stolen

699
00:51:03,260 --> 00:51:08,065
I have never felt guiltier
about anything
in my life, Donna.

700
00:51:08,065 --> 00:51:10,267
You have to believe that.

701
00:51:10,267 --> 00:51:13,637
I go away for one night
and this is what happens?

702
00:51:16,306 --> 00:51:18,108
I can't even look at you,
right now.

703
00:51:18,108 --> 00:51:19,709
I think you should leave.

704
00:52:36,920 --> 00:52:42,792
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

705
00:52:49,933 --> 00:52:51,168
[TIRES SCREECHES]

706
00:53:22,399 --> 00:53:23,934
Who the hell are you?
What's going on?

707
00:53:23,934 --> 00:53:27,971
Take it easy, Mr. McDermott.
Detective Braeden,
Metro Division.

708
00:53:27,971 --> 00:53:30,507
I'm assigned the investigation
of your son's disappearance.

709
00:53:31,408 --> 00:53:33,577
I'm under surveillance?

710
00:53:33,577 --> 00:53:36,346
Standard procedure
for this type of situation,
Mr. McDermott.

711
00:53:39,282 --> 00:53:42,719
Donna. Donna,
something's just happened

712
00:53:42,719 --> 00:53:45,388
Listen, whatever
you think of me, right now,
I need to come home.

713
00:53:45,388 --> 00:53:46,456
We gotta talk.

714
00:53:50,560 --> 00:53:52,696
It's just so unbelievable
that they would
be following you.

715
00:53:53,697 --> 00:53:54,731
Yeah, it is.

716
00:53:56,399 --> 00:53:59,636
I mean, we're the victims, here.
What're they thinking?

717
00:54:00,437 --> 00:54:01,504
I have no idea.

718
00:54:07,777 --> 00:54:09,679
Donna, I know I let you down.

719
00:54:11,348 --> 00:54:12,749
But we have to be
together on this.

720
00:54:12,749 --> 00:54:13,817
It's the only way
we're gonna get through it.

721
00:54:17,887 --> 00:54:20,423
[PHONE RINGS]

722
00:54:20,423 --> 00:54:22,292
OFFICER:
We got a call coming in.
Let's go.

723
00:54:26,696 --> 00:54:27,764
Hello?

724
00:54:30,767 --> 00:54:31,635
Yes, hold on.

725
00:54:34,904 --> 00:54:35,972
It's Rachel.

726
00:54:37,540 --> 00:54:38,708
She wants to talk to you.

727
00:54:47,751 --> 00:54:48,618
Hello?

728
00:54:51,888 --> 00:54:54,691
[CHATTERING]

729
00:55:03,500 --> 00:55:04,567
Hi.
Hi.

730
00:55:06,002 --> 00:55:08,705
Look, I gotta get back,
what'd you wanna talk about?

731
00:55:13,076 --> 00:55:14,744
It was just
one of those moments, Brian.

732
00:55:16,079 --> 00:55:19,316
I mean, you were there,
and I was there, and...

733
00:55:20,984 --> 00:55:22,519
I'm sorry.

734
00:55:22,519 --> 00:55:25,088
Hey, it was just
as much my fault.

735
00:55:25,088 --> 00:55:26,690
I never should have
let it happen.

736
00:55:27,457 --> 00:55:28,491
But what's done is done.

737
00:55:31,895 --> 00:55:32,962
Is that all?

738
00:55:35,065 --> 00:55:37,100
What I really want
to see you about is the police.

739
00:55:38,001 --> 00:55:39,602
What about them?

740
00:55:39,602 --> 00:55:42,572
Well, when I talked
to that Lt. Dugger,

741
00:55:42,572 --> 00:55:44,774
He asked me
if I'd actually
seen Justin that night.

742
00:55:46,710 --> 00:55:47,777
And?

743
00:55:50,513 --> 00:55:53,483
Well, that's the thing,
Justin was already asleep
when I got there.

744
00:55:53,483 --> 00:55:56,019
So I just
turned on the TV, and...

745
00:55:56,019 --> 00:55:58,588
And I had the monitor
right next to me
the whole time.

746
00:55:58,588 --> 00:56:00,090
You didn't check on him?

747
00:56:00,090 --> 00:56:02,659
Well, he was asleep,
I didn't want him to wake up.

748
00:56:02,659 --> 00:56:05,095
And I was about to
go and check on him
when you came in, and...

749
00:56:06,529 --> 00:56:08,064
Well, you know
what happened then.

750
00:56:08,064 --> 00:56:10,133
You know
he was in there, Rachel.

751
00:56:10,133 --> 00:56:11,534
That's true.

752
00:56:12,669 --> 00:56:14,804
But I never actually
saw him that night.

753
00:56:17,006 --> 00:56:18,608
I had to tell him the truth.

754
00:56:21,144 --> 00:56:22,645
I'm really sorry.

755
00:56:48,171 --> 00:56:50,407
So how did it go?

756
00:56:50,407 --> 00:56:52,842
You never told me
about the burn on his arm.

757
00:56:52,842 --> 00:56:54,711
Well, you were the one
in a rush, not me.

758
00:56:54,711 --> 00:56:56,780
Now, where's my money?

759
00:56:56,780 --> 00:56:59,883
I can't deliver the baby
until the bandages come off.

760
00:56:59,883 --> 00:57:04,053
That is your problem.
I wanna get paid,
and I want out.

761
00:57:04,821 --> 00:57:06,122
I thought I made it clear--

762
00:57:06,122 --> 00:57:09,592
You wanna turn in
my confession,
be my guest.

763
00:57:09,592 --> 00:57:11,628
Because I'm at a point
where I really don't
give a damn anymore.

764
00:57:11,628 --> 00:57:12,929
Calm down, Joan.

765
00:57:14,063 --> 00:57:16,566
In a few days,
I'll have your payment.

766
00:57:16,566 --> 00:57:21,171
I want my money now,
and this time, I want half.
$10,000

767
00:57:21,171 --> 00:57:22,605
That's ridiculous!

768
00:57:22,605 --> 00:57:24,808
Well, this isn't a negotiation.

769
00:57:24,808 --> 00:57:27,677
In fact, go ahead
and show them my confession.

770
00:57:27,677 --> 00:57:29,679
'Cause the way I see it,

771
00:57:29,679 --> 00:57:32,081
I could cut myself
a pretty decent deal

772
00:57:32,081 --> 00:57:34,584
if I tell the police
everything I know
about the kidnappings,

773
00:57:34,584 --> 00:57:35,885
don't you think?

774
00:57:39,522 --> 00:57:42,992
Fine, Joan. $10,000 it is.

775
00:57:50,767 --> 00:57:51,835
DONNA:
She's sorry?

776
00:57:53,102 --> 00:57:55,505
Fine. We all are.

777
00:57:55,505 --> 00:57:57,540
Nothing happened.

778
00:57:57,540 --> 00:58:00,977
Brian, you know,
it's not whether or not
you actually slept with her,

779
00:58:00,977 --> 00:58:05,248
think you were the type
of person to get into
a situation like that.

780
00:58:05,248 --> 00:58:06,883
I made a mistake.

781
00:58:07,517 --> 00:58:08,952
I'm still the same person.

782
00:58:11,921 --> 00:58:13,690
I don't know, I really don't.

783
00:58:19,095 --> 00:58:20,163
Anyway...

784
00:58:24,200 --> 00:58:26,736
An apology wasn't
the only reason Rachel
wanted to meet.

785
00:58:27,971 --> 00:58:29,172
She wanted to warn me.

786
00:58:30,907 --> 00:58:33,076
Dugger asked her
is she's actually seen
Justin that night.

787
00:58:33,643 --> 00:58:34,911
And she said no.

788
00:58:35,845 --> 00:58:38,615
He was already asleep
when she got here.

789
00:58:38,615 --> 00:58:42,085
And Dugger thinks
Justin was never
in that room that night.

790
00:58:42,085 --> 00:58:44,220
That's insane--
That is why these
cops are here.

791
00:58:44,220 --> 00:58:45,822
That's why he's
having me followed.

792
00:58:49,192 --> 00:58:51,094
And what?

793
00:58:51,094 --> 00:58:53,763
What, they think
we arranged
a fake kidnapping?

794
00:58:53,763 --> 00:58:56,833
Yeah. And tried to make it
look like that
other one in Northside.

795
00:58:57,967 --> 00:58:59,602
But this is crazy!

796
00:58:59,602 --> 00:59:02,138
Just watch the
evening news, honey.

797
00:59:02,138 --> 00:59:04,541
You remember that woman
who drowned her two kids
in her car

798
00:59:04,541 --> 00:59:08,778
And then there was the guy
who backed over his daughter
intentionally,

799
00:59:08,778 --> 00:59:10,647
and claimed
it was an accident.

800
00:59:10,647 --> 00:59:12,015
They think Justin's dead?

801
00:59:13,283 --> 00:59:14,717
He's not dead.

802
00:59:15,218 --> 00:59:16,719
What is he is dead?

803
00:59:16,719 --> 00:59:18,555
I will not accept that!

804
00:59:20,323 --> 00:59:21,558
We're gonna get him back.

805
00:59:27,864 --> 00:59:29,832
I'll make up the bed
and stay for you, okay?

806
01:00:10,940 --> 01:00:13,676
[ROCK-A-BY BABY MUSIC PLAYS]

807
01:00:25,688 --> 01:00:29,092
[ROCK-A-BY BABY MUSIC PLAYS]

808
01:00:40,703 --> 01:00:43,039
Brian, wake up. Wake up.

809
01:00:44,641 --> 01:00:45,708
The lullaby.

810
01:00:46,175 --> 01:00:47,810
What?

811
01:00:47,810 --> 01:00:50,146
The newspaper said
that in the Northside case

812
01:00:50,146 --> 01:00:53,650
the woman heard the kidnapper
singing the baby a lullaby.

813
01:00:53,650 --> 01:00:55,018
Remember that night
that you went out for coffee

814
01:00:55,018 --> 01:00:56,953
and I thought I heard you
on the monitor?

815
01:00:56,953 --> 01:00:58,955
The voice that I heard
was singiRock-a-bye Baby.

816
01:01:00,823 --> 01:01:03,393
That's the same song the guy
was singing when he took Justin.

817
01:01:03,393 --> 01:01:04,727
It's gotta be the same man.

818
01:01:07,263 --> 01:01:09,198
These monitors only
have a short range.

819
01:01:09,198 --> 01:01:12,001
If someone else
has as unit like ours,
they'd have to be close by.

820
01:01:12,001 --> 01:01:14,170
Have there been any other kids
in the neighborhood
reported missing?

821
01:01:15,204 --> 01:01:17,106
No, not that I know of.

822
01:01:17,106 --> 01:01:19,308
We can damn sure
knock on a few doors
and find out

823
01:01:19,308 --> 01:01:20,977
who else has
a monitor like ours.

824
01:01:27,417 --> 01:01:29,285
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYS]

825
01:01:42,198 --> 01:01:43,433
[INAUDIBLE]

826
01:02:13,296 --> 01:02:14,297
[INAUDIBLE]

827
01:02:30,113 --> 01:02:32,782
HELEN:
We were very lucky
to find him, Mrs. Simmonds.

828
01:02:32,782 --> 01:02:35,051
MRS. SIMMONDS:
Can you tell us anything
else about his birth parents?

829
01:02:35,051 --> 01:02:37,019
HELEN:
I'm afraid as
part of our agreement,

830
01:02:37,019 --> 01:02:39,789
they asked that their
identities be secret.

831
01:02:39,789 --> 01:02:44,861
Of course. The main thing is
that we're getting
a healthy child.

832
01:02:44,861 --> 01:02:46,262
Here's the first half.

833
01:02:46,262 --> 01:02:50,333
The final sum of $50,000
is payable on the day itself.

834
01:02:50,333 --> 01:02:52,502
Which should be
very soon now.

835
01:02:52,502 --> 01:02:56,105
We were under the impression
that we were gonna
pick him up today.

836
01:02:56,105 --> 01:02:59,342
Well, I'm afraid
there's been an
unavoidable delay.

837
01:02:59,342 --> 01:03:01,944
We're looking at
another week,
perhaps two.

838
01:03:01,944 --> 01:03:04,380
You promised us a child
by the end of this week.

839
01:03:04,380 --> 01:03:09,152
How do we know the birth parents
won't decide
to change their minds?

840
01:03:09,152 --> 01:03:12,121
That won't happen,
in this case,
I can assure you.

841
01:03:12,121 --> 01:03:14,857
If we can't
have that child by Friday,

842
01:03:14,857 --> 01:03:17,160
we're gonna have to
cancel our agreement.

843
01:03:17,160 --> 01:03:19,929
Minus the reasonable expenses
you've incurred, of course.

844
01:03:24,200 --> 01:03:26,002
I may have to pull
some strings.

845
01:03:27,837 --> 01:03:28,838
But you'll have your baby.

846
01:03:33,910 --> 01:03:37,814
WOMAN:
I don't know if I can help you,
folks, but ask away.

847
01:03:37,814 --> 01:03:40,149
Have you heard of
any children being
taken from here?

848
01:03:40,149 --> 01:03:41,150
Missing maybe?

849
01:03:42,385 --> 01:03:43,553
Yeah.

850
01:03:44,520 --> 01:03:47,123
Happened a couple of weeks ago.

851
01:03:47,123 --> 01:03:49,525
The people in 127,
right over there.

852
01:03:51,027 --> 01:03:53,129
What happened?
Custody thing

853
01:03:53,129 --> 01:03:56,365
Ex-husband broke in one night
and took the little girl.

854
01:03:56,365 --> 01:03:58,167
Did they notify the police?

855
01:03:58,167 --> 01:04:02,505
Well, yeah. I assume they did.
Why wouldn't they?

856
01:04:02,505 --> 01:04:03,372
Thanks.
Thank you.

857
01:04:16,452 --> 01:04:18,254
Yes?

858
01:04:18,254 --> 01:04:20,289
Hi. My name is Donna McDermott.

859
01:04:20,289 --> 01:04:22,425
And this is my husband, Brian.
Hi.

860
01:04:22,425 --> 01:04:24,861
We live down the street.

861
01:04:24,861 --> 01:04:26,529
We'd like to talk to you
about your daughter.

862
01:04:29,866 --> 01:04:30,933
You're not cops?

863
01:04:31,133 --> 01:04:32,201
No.

864
01:04:32,635 --> 01:04:33,903
Can we come in?

865
01:04:37,106 --> 01:04:38,174
Please?

866
01:04:41,444 --> 01:04:42,511
Yeah.

867
01:04:47,950 --> 01:04:50,086
Somebody took
out baby, too.

868
01:04:50,086 --> 01:04:51,454
Maybe we can help each other.

869
01:04:51,454 --> 01:04:53,489
I'm sure it was my ex-husband
who took Elizabeth.

870
01:04:54,223 --> 01:04:55,191
Did it once before.

871
01:04:56,425 --> 01:04:58,194
Did you actually
see him take her?

872
01:04:59,528 --> 01:05:02,665
No. We were at a party
two doors down.

873
01:05:02,665 --> 01:05:04,066
We brought the monitor.

874
01:05:05,067 --> 01:05:06,168
Guess it was too noisy
to hear it.

875
01:05:08,938 --> 01:05:09,972
Why didn't you report it?

876
01:05:13,609 --> 01:05:16,279
I've been living with Kurt
for about a year now, and...

877
01:05:18,080 --> 01:05:20,616
he doesn't have much
patience with kids.

878
01:05:20,616 --> 01:05:22,685
He's been very tough
on Elizabeth,
you know what I mean?

879
01:05:24,420 --> 01:05:26,489
I figured she'd be
better off with her dad.

880
01:05:28,357 --> 01:05:31,227
Are you positive
it was your ex-husband
who took her?

881
01:05:31,227 --> 01:05:33,529
He had been threatening
to o it again.

882
01:05:33,529 --> 01:05:36,465
This time he was clever.
Cut a hole in the glass,
came in through the window.

883
01:05:38,968 --> 01:05:41,570
Did you try to contact
your ex-husband
after this happened?

884
01:05:41,570 --> 01:05:43,105
He moved.

885
01:05:43,105 --> 01:05:44,707
Kurt made me promise
not to report him.

886
01:05:45,508 --> 01:05:46,676
Why?

887
01:05:46,676 --> 01:05:49,145
He's got a short fuse, and...

888
01:05:51,213 --> 01:05:53,049
couple of other complaints
on his records.

889
01:06:02,358 --> 01:06:04,694
If her ex-husband
has her daughter,
we've got nothing.

890
01:06:04,694 --> 01:06:07,463
Yeah, but if he doesn't,
this is a kidnapping
just like ours.

891
01:06:07,463 --> 01:06:09,131
Probably by the same guy.

892
01:06:09,131 --> 01:06:10,232
And it wasn't reported.

893
01:06:10,232 --> 01:06:12,001
I know.

894
01:06:12,001 --> 01:06:12,735
We've got to get to Dugger.

895
01:06:17,039 --> 01:06:19,976
[CHATTERING]

896
01:06:23,379 --> 01:06:26,649
Yeah. Yeah, okay, thanks.

897
01:06:28,718 --> 01:06:32,388
Well, Lucy Becknell's
ex-husband didn't even know
the kid's missing.

898
01:06:33,522 --> 01:06:37,493
Yeah, we checked it out.
He doesn't have the baby.

899
01:06:37,493 --> 01:06:40,029
It looks like
the guy who took her daughter

900
01:06:40,029 --> 01:06:41,263
may have taken your son, too.

901
01:06:42,598 --> 01:06:44,266
Why is this happening?

902
01:06:44,266 --> 01:06:46,035
Why haven't there been
any ransom calls?

903
01:06:46,035 --> 01:06:48,471
Well, I think this is something
being done for the black market.

904
01:06:51,340 --> 01:06:54,610
What you have to understand is
there's a market for babies.

905
01:06:54,610 --> 01:06:57,546
I mean,
to legally adopt a child
could take years,

906
01:06:57,546 --> 01:07:00,516
with no guarantees
even then,
so there are brokers.

907
01:07:02,284 --> 01:07:04,553
You think someone's trying
to sell our son?

908
01:07:04,553 --> 01:07:07,623
It's big money.
Six-figure fees
are not uncommon.

909
01:07:07,623 --> 01:07:12,028
Some wealthy people don't care,
they just wanna cut through
the red tape and get it done.

910
01:07:12,028 --> 01:07:14,630
Ans when people are willing
to pay there's always someone
willing to do what's needed.

911
01:07:16,565 --> 01:07:20,102
Why these babies?
What's the connection?

912
01:07:20,102 --> 01:07:24,040
Well, there's,
there's something
I've noticed here.

913
01:07:24,040 --> 01:07:29,345
Lucy Becknell's daughter
was being abused
by her boyfriend, she says.

914
01:07:29,345 --> 01:07:32,348
According to this,
the Northside kid was
also being abused.

915
01:07:33,249 --> 01:07:35,184
Justin wasn't being abused.

916
01:07:35,184 --> 01:07:38,687
No, but the kidnappers
probably thought he was.

917
01:07:38,687 --> 01:07:42,224
Head injuries, burns,
emergency room visits.

918
01:07:42,224 --> 01:07:44,627
The thing is,
people who abuse their children

919
01:07:44,627 --> 01:07:47,696
generally don't wanna
draw attention
to themselves.

920
01:07:47,696 --> 01:07:51,667
So they might not be
so quick to report
the child missing.

921
01:07:51,667 --> 01:07:54,236
Like I told you,
the longer a child is missing,

922
01:07:54,236 --> 01:07:56,405
the harder it is
to get them back.

923
01:07:56,405 --> 01:07:58,374
I think that's what
the kidnappers are counting on.

924
01:08:00,676 --> 01:08:02,111
[PHONE RINGS]

925
01:08:06,782 --> 01:08:09,518
We've already got
computer data
coming in from the FBI.

926
01:08:09,518 --> 01:08:11,554
Anything having to do
with illegal adoption,

927
01:08:11,554 --> 01:08:14,123
anything, anybody convicted
of baby stealing,

928
01:08:14,123 --> 01:08:16,125
brokers, attorneys,
agencies, you name it.

929
01:08:19,228 --> 01:08:22,631
Listen, I'm sorry
we had to put you both
through the wringer.

930
01:08:23,732 --> 01:08:25,668
We were only thinking
of your boy.

931
01:08:25,668 --> 01:08:27,169
Keep us informed.

932
01:08:27,169 --> 01:08:27,636
Every step of the way.

933
01:08:31,841 --> 01:08:33,476
Thanks, Lieutenant.

934
01:08:37,480 --> 01:08:40,616
You know, I did get a call
from a woman
at the medical center.

935
01:08:40,616 --> 01:08:42,218
Who?

936
01:08:42,218 --> 01:08:45,421
Someone from records.
I don't recall her name.

937
01:08:45,421 --> 01:08:47,723
She said she was concerned
with how many visits

938
01:08:47,723 --> 01:08:50,626
that Justin had made to the ER
and did I suspect abuse.

939
01:08:52,862 --> 01:08:56,198
I know you both love
Justin very much,

940
01:08:56,198 --> 01:08:57,466
and you would never
hurt him intentionally.

941
01:08:58,334 --> 01:09:00,603
Could this woman
have been a doctor?

942
01:09:00,603 --> 01:09:04,840
Doubtful. Still, she did ask
leading question.

943
01:09:04,840 --> 01:09:07,443
"Could it have been?,"
"Is it possible?,"
that kinda thing.

944
01:09:07,910 --> 01:09:09,211
And you said?

945
01:09:13,215 --> 01:09:16,185
I said anything is possible.

946
01:09:16,185 --> 01:09:19,855
I-I-I I didn't,
I didn't mean--
I was...

947
01:09:21,924 --> 01:09:23,592
I'm very--
I'm very sorry.

948
01:09:26,295 --> 01:09:27,363
Let's go.

949
01:09:34,203 --> 01:09:39,608
WOMAN:
Dr. Terrence Edwards to ICU.
Dr. Terrence Edwards to ICU.

950
01:09:41,644 --> 01:09:43,546
Excuse me?
May I help you?

951
01:09:43,546 --> 01:09:45,814
Yes, our son, Justin McDermott
was a patient here.

952
01:09:45,814 --> 01:09:47,449
We'd like to take
a look at his records.

953
01:09:47,449 --> 01:09:48,918
Of course. I'll just
need to see some ID.

954
01:09:48,918 --> 01:09:50,186
Sure.

955
01:09:56,692 --> 01:09:58,394
Aren't you
little Justin's parents?

956
01:09:58,861 --> 01:10:01,630
Oh, he's such a sweetheart.
How's he doing?

957
01:10:04,567 --> 01:10:06,268
Justin was kidnapped.

958
01:10:06,268 --> 01:10:07,836
Oh, my God, that's horrible.

959
01:10:09,371 --> 01:10:11,707
How long ago
was your son admitted?

960
01:10:11,707 --> 01:10:13,309
Less than a week ago.

961
01:10:13,309 --> 01:10:14,677
I can't seem to
find his records.

962
01:10:14,677 --> 01:10:19,715
Well, I wouldn't worry about it.
His file is probably
up in pediatrics.

963
01:10:19,715 --> 01:10:21,917
With all the people
going in and out of this room

964
01:10:21,917 --> 01:10:24,286
it's a wonder
anything's where
it's supposed to be.

965
01:10:25,454 --> 01:10:26,855
I tell you what?

966
01:10:26,855 --> 01:10:30,259
Why don't I
track it down myself

967
01:10:30,259 --> 01:10:32,294
and I'll call you
as soon as I find it?

968
01:10:32,294 --> 01:10:33,429
We'd appreciate that.

969
01:10:33,429 --> 01:10:34,530
Certainly.

970
01:10:38,634 --> 01:10:41,270
PA SYSTEM:
Nurse Emerson
to Physical Therapy.

971
01:10:44,340 --> 01:10:46,008
Excuse me?

972
01:10:46,008 --> 01:10:48,544
Have the police turned up
anything yet?

973
01:10:48,544 --> 01:10:51,847
I mean, you must
be worried sick.

974
01:10:51,847 --> 01:10:54,016
They think our son
was kidnapped
for black market adoption.

975
01:10:54,984 --> 01:10:58,988
They say people pay
over $100,000
for a baby like Justin.

976
01:11:01,657 --> 01:11:04,293
It's unbelievable
what people are capable of.

977
01:11:22,278 --> 01:11:23,345
Robert!

978
01:11:25,614 --> 01:11:26,682
Robert!

979
01:11:30,519 --> 01:11:32,454
Hello, Robert.
Has Helen called yet?

980
01:11:32,921 --> 01:11:34,523
No. What's going on?

981
01:11:35,758 --> 01:11:38,427
She's probably still
in her meeting.

982
01:11:38,427 --> 01:11:42,398
Helen wants me to, uh,
take the baby
to the hospital, right away.

983
01:11:42,398 --> 01:11:44,033
Seems he has
an insulin deficiency.

984
01:11:44,033 --> 01:11:47,336
And if we don't treat him soon
he could go into diabetic shock.

985
01:11:48,003 --> 01:11:49,338
Where is he?

986
01:11:49,338 --> 01:11:50,406
Taking a nap.

987
01:11:51,674 --> 01:11:54,743
That's not a good sign.
Get him ready to go.

988
01:11:54,743 --> 01:11:57,079
Helen wants me to get
the baby's records
from her files.

989
01:11:57,079 --> 01:11:59,648
Oh, and we need
the car seat
and the carrier, too.

990
01:12:34,583 --> 01:12:35,884
[DOOR CLOSES]

991
01:13:09,151 --> 01:13:10,652
Robert?

992
01:13:13,422 --> 01:13:15,657
Robert?

993
01:13:15,657 --> 01:13:18,527
Robert, bring the baby down.
I need to check his burn.

994
01:13:18,527 --> 01:13:20,429
We have to deliver
him by Friday.

995
01:13:20,429 --> 01:13:21,663
Joan just picked him up.

996
01:13:26,068 --> 01:13:27,870
What?

997
01:13:27,870 --> 01:13:30,172
She took him to the hospital.
She said you knew all about it.

998
01:13:34,743 --> 01:13:37,446
Couple oh hours ago?
What's happening?

999
01:13:39,982 --> 01:13:41,049
I'm not sure.

1000
01:13:49,925 --> 01:13:53,128
[TENSE MUSIC PLAYS]

1001
01:13:59,701 --> 01:14:02,871
[TELEPHONE RINGS]

1002
01:14:06,942 --> 01:14:09,812
You must really think
I'm an idiot.

1003
01:14:11,046 --> 01:14:12,548
Joan, where's the baby?

1004
01:14:12,548 --> 01:14:14,183
You've been cheating me blind.

1005
01:14:14,183 --> 01:14:18,787
Helen, I've seen the file!
You're getting a $100,000
for this baby.

1006
01:14:21,223 --> 01:14:23,792
There's obviously been
a misunderstanding.

1007
01:14:23,792 --> 01:14:24,927
Listen to me, Joan.

1008
01:14:24,927 --> 01:14:26,628
No, you listen to me.

1009
01:14:26,628 --> 01:14:28,730
Meet me at the garage
in an hour.

1010
01:14:28,730 --> 01:14:31,099
And bring the money.

1011
01:14:31,099 --> 01:14:34,803
Whatever you say.
Just take care of the baby.

1012
01:14:34,803 --> 01:14:38,207
If you wanna see
this baby again, it's gonna
cost you $50,000.

1013
01:14:39,041 --> 01:14:40,843
I only want what's fair.

1014
01:14:40,843 --> 01:14:41,844
So do I, Joan.

1015
01:14:43,979 --> 01:14:47,115
[STRING MUSIC PLAYS]

1016
01:14:55,524 --> 01:14:58,627
[MUSIC INTENSIFIES]

1017
01:15:17,646 --> 01:15:19,114
You know, we became a family

1018
01:15:20,883 --> 01:15:22,184
without ever really
thinking it through.

1019
01:15:25,721 --> 01:15:28,757
I guess we never realized
how much hard work
there's in being a parent.

1020
01:15:32,594 --> 01:15:34,263
He changed our lives so much.

1021
01:15:36,131 --> 01:15:38,567
I just can't imagine
our life without him, you know?

1022
01:15:40,669 --> 01:15:42,237
We have to have another chance.

1023
01:15:48,944 --> 01:15:52,214
If we're gonna get through this,
we're gonna have to
do it together.

1024
01:16:52,174 --> 01:16:53,308
Where's the baby?

1025
01:16:53,308 --> 01:16:55,010
Where's my money?

1026
01:16:55,010 --> 01:16:56,378
You'll get it
when he's delivered.

1027
01:16:56,378 --> 01:16:59,381
I want it now.
$50,000. That's half.

1028
01:16:59,381 --> 01:17:01,750
Joan, be reasonable.

1029
01:17:01,750 --> 01:17:03,285
I'm the one who takes
all the risks,

1030
01:17:03,285 --> 01:17:05,621
pays all the expenses.
What do you do?

1031
01:17:05,621 --> 01:17:07,723
You point your finger,
and you say, "That one."

1032
01:17:07,723 --> 01:17:09,992
And if didn't,
you'd have nothing!

1033
01:17:09,992 --> 01:17:12,728
God only knows
how much you cheated me
before this.

1034
01:17:12,728 --> 01:17:14,329
I should be taking
the whole $100,000.

1035
01:17:14,329 --> 01:17:15,864
You should be
in jail, right now.

1036
01:17:16,398 --> 01:17:17,933
You committed murder,

1037
01:17:17,933 --> 01:17:19,968
and I'm the one
that got you off,
scot-free.

1038
01:17:19,968 --> 01:17:21,703
I only want what's mine.

1039
01:17:21,703 --> 01:17:23,705
This baby is not yours.

1040
01:17:31,313 --> 01:17:32,948
Joan! Give me that!

1041
01:18:03,378 --> 01:18:06,114
[CHATTERING]

1042
01:18:06,114 --> 01:18:07,883
BRIAN: Lieutenant.

1043
01:18:07,883 --> 01:18:09,451
Any of those leads
panned out?

1044
01:18:09,451 --> 01:18:11,286
How much sleep
have you two gotten?

1045
01:18:11,286 --> 01:18:12,988
We'll sleep
when Justin gets home.

1046
01:18:12,988 --> 01:18:15,023
Uh, nothing's
jumping off the page, yet.

1047
01:18:15,023 --> 01:18:17,325
We're running down
the list of employees
at the hospital.

1048
01:18:17,325 --> 01:18:18,927
[PHONE RINGS]

1049
01:18:20,062 --> 01:18:22,097
Dugger. Yeah, Braeden,
what's up?

1050
01:18:24,232 --> 01:18:26,935
Let me put you
on the box I got the McDermotts
here with me.

1051
01:18:29,738 --> 01:18:32,774
Yeah, like I was saying,
we found the body
about an hour ago.

1052
01:18:32,774 --> 01:18:35,310
The victim's presumed to be
an attorney named
Helen Sawyer.

1053
01:18:35,310 --> 01:18:37,279
We found a car nearby,
had legal documents,

1054
01:18:37,279 --> 01:18:39,281
with some adoption
paperwork in it.

1055
01:18:39,281 --> 01:18:42,451
Sawyer...
Yeah, here t is.

1056
01:18:42,451 --> 01:18:45,987
Specializes in custody
and adoption, office is
on Market Street.

1057
01:18:45,987 --> 01:18:48,090
It could be a coincidence,
but I thought
you might wanna know.

1058
01:18:49,057 --> 01:18:50,125
Thanks.

1059
01:18:56,932 --> 01:18:58,800
Going through
the State Bar Association.

1060
01:18:58,800 --> 01:19:01,403
It looks like Helen Sawyer
was a criminal attorney
for a while.

1061
01:19:02,804 --> 01:19:06,007
Times Herald.
Downloading a few
articles on her.

1062
01:19:06,007 --> 01:19:07,909
Time to go into
the superior court records.

1063
01:19:07,909 --> 01:19:09,978
See if I can find something...
Wait a minute.

1064
01:19:09,978 --> 01:19:11,346
Brian, look at this.
Come here.

1065
01:19:11,346 --> 01:19:12,447
What did you find?

1066
01:19:13,181 --> 01:19:14,149
Look at this picture!

1067
01:19:16,118 --> 01:19:18,086
That's the woman
from the hospital!
Oh, my...

1068
01:19:18,086 --> 01:19:21,323
And it says
here name is Joan Hollins.

1069
01:19:21,323 --> 01:19:23,792
Says she was accused
of stabbing her husband

1070
01:19:23,792 --> 01:19:25,427
Claimed he was abusing her.

1071
01:19:25,427 --> 01:19:27,095
Helen Sawyer was her attorney.

1072
01:19:28,029 --> 01:19:29,097
Gotta get Dugger.

1073
01:19:33,068 --> 01:19:34,402
Yes, Lt. Dugger, please.

1074
01:19:36,171 --> 01:19:37,539
Well, where is he,
this is urgent

1075
01:19:40,509 --> 01:19:43,378
It's the McDermotts.
We have some
very important information.

1076
01:19:43,378 --> 01:19:44,546
Can you right this down?

1077
01:19:44,546 --> 01:19:47,015
Mr. Simmonds?
Yes, this is Joan Hollins,

1078
01:19:47,015 --> 01:19:49,251
I'm Helen Sawyer's associate.

1079
01:19:49,251 --> 01:19:52,320
Well, actually,
I'm calling at Helen's request.

1080
01:19:52,320 --> 01:19:56,057
Unfortunately, she's been
unavoidably detained.

1081
01:19:56,057 --> 01:19:58,226
Oh, no, no, no,
everything's fine.

1082
01:19:58,226 --> 01:20:01,062
Um, I'll be the one
delivering your baby.

1083
01:20:01,062 --> 01:20:04,533
And she's authorized me
to accept the final $50,000
installment as well.

1084
01:20:09,137 --> 01:20:11,106
So why don't I meet you
at your hotel

1085
01:20:11,106 --> 01:20:13,842
and we'll take care
of everything in short order.

1086
01:20:13,842 --> 01:20:17,112
Say two o'clock? Excellent.

1087
01:20:17,946 --> 01:20:19,114
Then I will see you then.

1088
01:20:23,251 --> 01:20:25,220
Well, well, well, little one.

1089
01:20:29,224 --> 01:20:32,460
It is almost pay day! Yeah!

1090
01:20:57,252 --> 01:20:58,119
You live here?

1091
01:21:00,322 --> 01:21:03,358
Yeah. What's going on?

1092
01:21:03,358 --> 01:21:05,227
This is
Helen Sawyer's house, isn't it?

1093
01:21:05,961 --> 01:21:07,195
Yeah, she's
not home right now.

1094
01:21:08,163 --> 01:21:09,231
Are you a relative?

1095
01:21:10,565 --> 01:21:11,566
No.
Boyfriend?

1096
01:21:13,568 --> 01:21:15,070
She's my lawyer.
Who are you?

1097
01:21:16,504 --> 01:21:18,273
Detective Harland Dugger.

1098
01:21:19,274 --> 01:21:21,877
What's your name?

1099
01:21:21,877 --> 01:21:25,113
Robert. Look I think
you should come back, uh,
when Helen's home.

1100
01:21:25,113 --> 01:21:26,915
She's not coming home.
Robert what?

1101
01:21:28,650 --> 01:21:30,318
Hammack.
Where is she?

1102
01:21:30,986 --> 01:21:32,053
Helen's dead.

1103
01:21:33,922 --> 01:21:36,124
Mind if we go inside, Robert?

1104
01:21:39,194 --> 01:21:42,163
Look, unless you have
a search warrant,
you not going nowhere near--

1105
01:21:42,163 --> 01:21:43,431
I don't really
need your permission.

1106
01:21:48,103 --> 01:21:49,337
Why don't you come in with us?

1107
01:21:51,006 --> 01:21:51,973
Go on, I'll catch up.

1108
01:21:51,973 --> 01:21:53,208
OFFICER:
Come with me, sir

1109
01:22:05,620 --> 01:22:09,224
I thought maybe
you might know
something about that.

1110
01:22:09,991 --> 01:22:11,626
I don't know anything.

1111
01:22:11,626 --> 01:22:14,963
And what did Helen
represent you on, Robert?

1112
01:22:14,963 --> 01:22:17,365
Armed robbery,
breaking and entering,
grand theft?

1113
01:22:18,300 --> 01:22:20,402
I have nothing to say.

1114
01:22:20,402 --> 01:22:23,571
Huh. It's too bad
she's not gonna be around

1115
01:22:23,571 --> 01:22:26,007
to handle the kidnapping charges
I'm about to lay on you.

1116
01:22:28,343 --> 01:22:29,210
Hmm.

1117
01:22:32,180 --> 01:22:34,249
We found the toy
you tried to cover up
in the truck, too.

1118
01:22:37,085 --> 01:22:38,153
Where's the baby?

1119
01:22:40,689 --> 01:22:43,124
You do understand
if something
happens to that kid,

1120
01:22:43,124 --> 01:22:45,160
you're looking
at the death penalty.

1121
01:22:45,160 --> 01:22:51,299
Now, if you wanna cooperate
with me, I might be able
to do you some good.

1122
01:22:51,299 --> 01:22:54,502
The sooner we find him,
the less chance you'll
be spending time on death row.

1123
01:22:54,502 --> 01:22:56,104
What's it gonna be, Robert?

1124
01:23:00,108 --> 01:23:01,343
Joan took him.

1125
01:23:01,343 --> 01:23:03,345
Joan who?

1126
01:23:03,345 --> 01:23:06,448
I don't know her last name,
she's a client of Helen's.

1127
01:23:06,448 --> 01:23:08,984
Now, I don't wanna talk anymore
until I have a lawyer.

1128
01:23:13,755 --> 01:23:15,724
Cuff him. Read him his rights.

1129
01:23:19,627 --> 01:23:20,729
Stand up.

1130
01:23:25,767 --> 01:23:28,036
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

1131
01:23:29,537 --> 01:23:30,405
Dugger

1132
01:23:31,539 --> 01:23:32,607
What, when did they call?

1133
01:23:35,543 --> 01:23:37,445
Get an address,
I'll be in the car.

1134
01:23:39,180 --> 01:23:41,383
[BABY COOING]

1135
01:23:43,518 --> 01:23:45,286
Will keep right in there.

1136
01:23:48,223 --> 01:23:49,357
Okay.

1137
01:23:52,260 --> 01:23:54,396
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

1138
01:24:16,651 --> 01:24:18,653
[BABY COOING]

1139
01:24:37,272 --> 01:24:40,175
Hello? Anyone home?

1140
01:24:43,311 --> 01:24:45,180
[BABY CRIES]

1141
01:24:45,480 --> 01:24:46,548
Come on!

1142
01:24:46,548 --> 01:24:49,484
[INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

1143
01:25:27,856 --> 01:25:29,657
Maybe she didn't come
all the way up.

1144
01:25:29,657 --> 01:25:31,759
Maybe, but I'm gonna find out.

1145
01:26:06,895 --> 01:26:09,364
Justin! Justin!

1146
01:26:09,364 --> 01:26:12,567
DONNA:
Justin! Justin! Justin!

1147
01:26:15,937 --> 01:26:18,706
Maybe you're right.
Maybe she's not up here.

1148
01:26:19,507 --> 01:26:21,476
[BABY CRYING]
[GASPS]

1149
01:26:21,476 --> 01:26:24,379
Don't touch me.
Don't touch me.

1150
01:26:24,379 --> 01:26:26,681
You stay away from me!
Stay away from me!

1151
01:26:26,681 --> 01:26:28,383
Please give me my baby. Please.

1152
01:26:30,485 --> 01:26:31,553
JOAN: Stop!

1153
01:26:32,587 --> 01:26:35,490
[BABY CRYING]

1154
01:26:47,302 --> 01:26:48,369
BRIAN: Stop!

1155
01:26:48,369 --> 01:26:49,437
DONNA:
Oh, my God!

1156
01:26:49,437 --> 01:26:50,638
BRIAN: Please!

1157
01:26:50,638 --> 01:26:52,674
[BABY CRYING]

1158
01:27:14,696 --> 01:27:16,531
Okay! You win!

1159
01:27:16,998 --> 01:27:19,300
[BABY CRYING]

1160
01:27:19,300 --> 01:27:21,369
We'd rather you got
away with him
than fall!

1161
01:27:24,606 --> 01:27:26,774
Come back, please!
We won't try to stop you!

1162
01:27:26,774 --> 01:27:27,842
Come back!

1163
01:27:54,836 --> 01:27:55,903
Whoa.

1164
01:28:27,035 --> 01:28:29,771
[BABY CRYING]

1165
01:28:35,510 --> 01:28:37,078
[JOAN YELPS]

1166
01:28:37,078 --> 01:28:38,379
DUGGER:
Joan Hollins,
you're under arrest.

1167
01:28:38,379 --> 01:28:39,747
OFFICER:
Weapons down!

1168
01:28:39,747 --> 01:28:41,582
You have the right
to remain silent.

1169
01:28:41,582 --> 01:28:45,486
anything you say can,
and will, be held against you
in the court of law.

1170
01:28:50,758 --> 01:28:53,828
[DONNA GASPING] Hi. Oh!

1171
01:28:57,098 --> 01:28:58,833
[BABY GIGGLING]

